Global .gitignore (recommended)

-------------------------------------------
1) OS and Editor
System files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Icon?
Desktop.ini

Windows junk
*.lnk
*.temp
*.tmp

macOS Spotlight/Trash
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

IDEs and editors
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates
*.sas
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace
*.code-workspace

-------------------------------------------
2) Node, npm, yarn, pnpm
Node modules (do not track in monorepo, each package manages its own)
node_modules/

Lockfiles may be versioned by each package manager per package; keep consistent across monorepo
If you want a global ignore for all lockfiles, uncomment the line below
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
pnpm-lock.yaml.lock
yarn.lock
.yarn-integrity
Generated by npm/yarn/pnp
.pnp/
.pnp.js

Cache and artifacts
.npm
.npmrc
.yarn-cache/
.yarn/
.lock
.cache/

Dist, build, and typegen outputs per package
**/dist/
**/build/
**/coverage/
**/tests/output/

Babel, TypeScript, and other compile outputs
dist/
build/
compiled/
tsbuildinfo
*.tsbuildinfo
*.d.ts.d
*.d.ts

Generated by TypeScript/Vite/webpack
*.tsbuildinfo
*.js.map
.js.map.

-------------------------------------------
3) React frontend and shared UI code
Vite / webpack / CRA outputs
frontend/dist/
frontend/build/
frontend/.next/
frontend/.cache/

If your frontend shares code via a common package (e.g., packages/ui)
packages//dist/
packages//build/
packages/**/lib/

-------------------------------------------
4) Tests and coverage
coverage/
test-results/
junit.xml
*.spec.js.snap

Jest, Mocha, Vitest caches
/.cache
/.nyc_output
/coverage/

-------------------------------------------
5) Logs, secrets, and environment
logs/
.log
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

.env
.env.*
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.production.local
.env.test.local
.env..local
.env..local

Sensitive files (if you store secrets here, ensure they are ignored)
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
*.sec

-------------------------------------------
6) Docker and containers
docker-compose.override.yml
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.*
docker/
*.log
*.tar
*.zip

Exclude docker build artifacts if you commit
.dockerignore

If you run docker compose, may want to ignore the volumes
*.snap
**/docker-compose.yml

-------------------------------------------
7) CI / deployment
.github/
.gitlab/
.circleci/
,Jenkinsfile
*.yml
*.yaml

CircleCI or GitHub Actions caches
.github/cache/
.github/workflows/

-------------------------------------------
8) Monorepo specific
If you have a monorepo with multiple packages, ignore per-package build outputs
packages//dist/
packages//build/
packages//lib/
packages//coverage/

If you store shared caches per package
packages/*/.cache/

Optional: ignore yarn workspace/global caches (adjust if you manage caches differently)
**/node_modules/.cache/

-------------------------------------------
9) IDE performance / artifacts
*.orig
*.rej
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.tmp
*.DS_Store

-------------------------------------------
10) Optional: local environment placeholders
If you maintain a local dotfile directory for devs, ignore it
.localdev/